I’m back home and back to working on this paddle. This one, and seven others, will be auctioned off on January 21th for Haley Daniels’ ‘It Takes a Village’ fundraiser.
🛶
Haley has been at the forefront of gender equality reform to push for equal opportunity in sport. She’s pioneering a legacy towards Tokyo 2020 in women’s whitewater slalom canoeing, where her sport will make its debut in the Olympics. She is a bronze medallist from the Toronto 2015 Pan American games and is on her way to the podium again this year for the 2019 Pan American games in Lima, Peru.
🛶
I hope that my little contribution will help her get closer to Tokyo. If you’re interested in learning more about Haley’s story and the fundraiser, have a look at her page @haleydanski

Jefferson Airplane, Richmond Arena Vancouver
.
.
Grade – PAE Excellent 79
Bands/Bill – Jefferson Airplane, Magic Fern, Collectors, Painted Ship
Venue – Richmond Arena
City – Vancouver, British Columbia
Date – 5/27/67
Dimensions – 13 19/32 x 19 29/32”
Printing – OP-1, Original Pre-Concert First Printing
Artist – Bob Masse
Paper Type – Thin
.
.
BIDDING ENDS THURS 12/13 @ 9 PM EST
.
.
This incredible poster by Canadian artist Bob Masse is one of the most striking designs in the rock poster world, and is coveted by top collectors of the genre! The event was billed as the Vancouver Trips Festival. The poster promotes a May 1967 show that featured The Jefferson Airplane at the Richmond Arena in Vancouver, British Columbia. It was a low print run, printed on very thin paper, making any surviving examples difficult to keep in top condition. This was the Airplane at the point of their commercial breakthrough and creative peak, just one month after the release of their historic recording “Surrealistic Pillow”. The Airplane were joined by other lesser known acts at this event. .
.
.

The wait is over! Art For Youth London is back and open from tomorrow till Friday at the lovely @mallgalleries. 
Art For Youth was one of my very first exhibitions. Now it’s my 7th consecutive year in the show and I’m always honoured to be involved. It’s just an amazing event! 
Last night, during the private sponsors’ evening, my little circular photograph ‘Conquer’ was auctioned alongside Tracey Emin’s (see the second picture) and Ken Howard’s work and raised nice £600 for the charity 😊
100% from the auctions and 35% from the overall sales in the show supports UK Youth charity. 
Also, there is a Mystery Post Card section where you can buy mystery art for just £35 - 100% goes to UK Youth. 
To find more about the exhibition and UK Youth charity visit: www.artforyouth.com/about-us
And for tickets: www.artforyouth.com/exhibition
Hope to see you there! 🙂
.
Art For Youth is officially closing my very busy and successful season of exhibitions. Going to get some rest now. See you next year!
.
